  <a href="#1" id="1">
   MIRROR GROUP'S CHRONOLOGY
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Maxwell's Maxwell Communication Corp. sold its Pergamon Press PLC unit for #440 million.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Maxwell's son Ian, who has been appointed deputy chairman of Mirror Group, will resign from his post at Maxwell Communication, where he was joint deputy managing director.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   In 1990, Mirror had profit of #37.2 million, or 28.2 pence a share, on revenue of #445 million.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   Robert Maxwell bought Mirror Group in 1984 from Reed International PLC for #113 million.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   Maxwell Communication said in Mar. 1991 that its management would be taken over by Kevin Maxwell, Ian's brother.
  </a>
